%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E23%3A11%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20king%20also%20burned%20the%20chariots%20dedicated%20to%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_23_12%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EJosiah%20tore%20down%20the%20altars%20that%20the%20kings%20of%20Judah%20had%20built%20on%20the%20palace%20roof%20above%20the%20upper%20room%20of%20Ahaz.%20The%20king%20destroyed%20the%20altars%20that%20Manasseh%20had%20built%20in%20the%20two%20courtyards%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple.%20He%20smashed%20them%20to%20bits%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E23%3A12%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EHe%20quickly%20removed%20them.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20scattered%20the%20pieces%20in%20the%20Kidron%20Valley.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_23_13%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20also%20desecrated%20the%20pagan%20shrines%20east%20of%20Jerusalem%2C%20to%20the%20south%20of%20the%20Mount%20of%20Corruption%2C%20where%20King%20Solomon%20of%20Israel%20had%20built%20shrines%20for%20Ashtoreth%2C%20the%20detestable%20goddess%20of%20the%20Sidonians%3B%20and%20for%20Chemosh%2C%20the%20detestable%20god%20of%20the%20Moabites%3B%20and%20for%20Molech%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E23%3A13%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EMilcom%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Molech.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20vile%20god%20of%20the%20Ammonites.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_23_14%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20smashed%20the%20sacred%20pillars%20and%20cut%20down%20the%20Asherah%20poles.%20Then%20he%20desecrated%20these%20places%20by%20scattering%20human%20bones%20over%20them.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_23_15%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20also%20tore%20down%20the%20altar%20at%20Bethel%26%23x2014%3Bthe%20pagan%20shrine%20that%20Jeroboam%20son%20of%20Nebat%20had%20made%20when%20he%20caused%20Israel%20to%20sin.%20He%20burned%20down%20the%20shrine%20and%20ground%20it%20to%20dust%2C%20and%20he%20burned%20the%20Asherah%20pole.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_23_16%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Josiah%20turned%20around%20and%20noticed%20several%20tombs%20in%20the%20side%20of%20the%20hill.%20He%20ordered%20that%20the%20bones%20be%20brought%20out%2C%20and%20he%20burned%20them%20on%20the%20altar%20at%20Bethel%20to%20desecrate%20it.%20(This%20happened%20just%20as%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20promised%20through%20the%20man%20of%20God%20when%20Jeroboam%20stood%20beside%20the%20altar%20at%20the%20festival.)%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EThen%20Josiah%20turned%20and%20looked%20up%20at%20the%20tomb%20of%20the%20man%20of%20God%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E23%3A16%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%3B%20Hebrew%20lacks%20%3Cem%3Ewhen%20Jeroboam%20stood%20beside%20the%20altar%20at%20the%20festival.%20Then%20Josiah%20turned%20and%20looked%20up%20at%20the%20tomb%20of%20the%20man%20of%20God.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20who%20had%20predicted%20these%20things.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_23_17%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20is%20that%20monument%20over%20there%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Josiah%20asked.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EAnd%20the%20people%20of%20the%20town%20told%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BIt%20is%20the%20tomb%20of%20the%20man%20of%20God%20who%20came%20from%20Judah%20and%20predicted%20the%20very%20things%20that%20you%20have%20just%20done%20to%20the%20altar%20at%20Bethel!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_23_18%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EJosiah%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BLeave%20it%20alone.%20Don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20disturb%20his%20bones.%26%23x201D%3B%20So%20they%20did%20not%20burn%20his%20bones%20or%20those%20of%20the%20old%20prophet%20from%20Samaria.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_23_19%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Josiah%20demolished%20all%20the%20buildings%20at%20the%20pagan%20shrines%20in%20the%20towns%20of%20Samaria%2C%20just%20as%20he%20had%20done%20at%20Bethel.%20They%20had%20been%20built%20by%20the%20various%20kings%20of%20Israel%20and%20had%20made%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E23%3A19%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20and%20Syriac%20versions%20and%20Latin%20Vulgate%3B%20Hebrew%20lacks%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%20class%3D%22tn-sc-ital%22%3ELord%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20very%20angry.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_23_20%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20executed%20the%20priests%20of%20the%20pagan%20shrines%20on%20their%20own%20altars%2C%20and%20he%20burned%20human%20bones%2